==English==

===Etymology===
Named after ''[[w:Alois Alzheimer|Alois Alzheimer]]'' (June 14, 1864 - December 19, 1915), a German neurologist who described the disease in 1906.

===Pronunciation===
*älts'hī-mə(r)z, /ˈɑːltshaɪmə(r)z/, /"A:ltshaIm@(r)z/
*ălts'hī-mə(r)z, /ˈæltshaɪmə(r)z/, /"{ltshaIm@(r)z/
*ôlts'hī-mə(r)z, /ˈɔːltshaɪmə(r)z/, /"O:ltshaIm@(r)z/
*ôlz'hī-mə(r)z, /ˈɔːlzhaɪmə(r)z/, /"O:lzhaIm@(r)z/

===Noun===
'''[[Alzheimer]]’s [[disease]]'''

# A disorder of loss mental functions resulting from brain tissue changes<!-- encyclopedic info?: the causes of which are not yet fully elucidated-->; senile dementia of Alzheimer's type.

====Synonyms====
*[[Alzheimer’s]] (''colloquial'')
*[[senile dementia]] (''especially formerly'')

